   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#  `pore_size_distribution`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Calculates the pore size distribution in the image produced by either `local thickness` or `porosimetry` method where each voxel in the image shows the radius of the largest sphere (circle in 2D) that would overlap it."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:54:49.861297Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:54:49.861030Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:54:52.069830Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:54:52.068954Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<Signature (im, bins=10, log=True, voxel_size=1)>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 1,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import porespy as ps\n",
    "import inspect\n",
    "inspect.signature(ps.metrics.pore_size_distribution)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `im`\n",
    "The input image csontaining the sizes of the largest sphere that overlaps each voxel. This image can be generated by implementing ``porosimetry`` or ``local_thickness`` filter on a binary image. Let's generate a test image:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:54:52.072778Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:54:52.072511Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:54:52.564224Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:54:52.563710Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json": {
       "model_id": "aa193f6c0ec94d12a7ec34ed8a2f671f",
       "version_major": 2,
       "version_minor": 0
      },
      "text/plain": [
       "  0%|          | 0/25 [00:00<?, ?it/s]"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 288x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "np.random.seed(10)\n",
    "im = ps.generators.blobs(shape=[500, 500])\n",
    "im = ps.filters.porosimetry(im)\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=[4, 4])\n",
    "ax.imshow(im, origin='lower', interpolation='none')\n",
    "ax.axis(False);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now we can calculate the size distributions in the test image. `pore_size_distribution` returns a custom object with information of the distribution of the pore sizes. The x axis in the following images is the Log(pore radius).The histogram of logarithm (base-10) of pore sizes is useful to plot wide size distributions or to better visualize the data in the small size region. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:54:52.566378Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:54:52.566188Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:54:53.002467Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:54:53.001780Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x288 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "data = ps.metrics.pore_size_distribution(im=im)\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=[10, 4])\n",
    "ax[0].plot(data.bin_centers,data.pdf)\n",
    "ax[1].plot(data.bin_centers,data.cdf)\n",
    "ax[2].bar(data.bin_centers, data.cdf, data.bin_widths, edgecolor='k')\n",
    "ax[0].set_title(\"Probability Density Function\")\n",
    "ax[1].set_title(\"Cumulative Density Function\")\n",
    "ax[2].set_title('Bar Plot');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `bins`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The default number of bins for the histogram is 10. Let's increase the bins to 100:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:54:53.005879Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:54:53.005272Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:54:53.388807Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:54:53.388320Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x288 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "data = ps.metrics.pore_size_distribution(im=im, bins=100)\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=[10, 4])\n",
    "ax[0].plot(data.bin_centers,data.pdf)\n",
    "ax[1].plot(data.bin_centers,data.cdf)\n",
    "ax[2].bar(data.bin_centers, data.cdf, data.bin_widths, edgecolor='k')\n",
    "ax[0].set_title(\"Probability Density Function\")\n",
    "ax[1].set_title(\"Cumulative Density Function\")\n",
    "ax[2].set_title('Bar Plot');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Plot results:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `log`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "By default, the histogram binning is based on log(pore radius). We can calculate the size distribution base on pore radius with `log=False`. The resulting histogram binning is then performed on the pore radius values instead of log(pore radius.\n",
    "Note that for calculating the pore sizes base on diameter, `bin_centers` returned by `pore_size_distribution` must be multiplied by 2."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:54:53.392042Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:54:53.391842Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:54:53.710388Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:54:53.709892Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x288 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "data = ps.metrics.pore_size_distribution(im=im, log=False)\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=[10, 4])\n",
    "ax[0].plot(data.bin_centers,data.pdf)\n",
    "ax[1].plot(data.bin_centers,data.cdf)\n",
    "ax[2].bar(data.bin_centers, data.cdf, data.bin_widths, edgecolor='k')\n",
    "ax[0].set_title(\"Probability Density Function\")\n",
    "ax[1].set_title(\"Cumulative Density Function\")\n",
    "ax[2].set_title('Bar Plot');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `voxel_size`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "By default the voxel_size is 1. We can assign voxel size of the image as the input or apply the scaling on the results after the fact:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:54:53.713377Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:54:53.713172Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:54:53.903236Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:54:53.902761Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x288 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "voxel_size=1e-3\n",
    "data = ps.metrics.pore_size_distribution(im=im, voxel_size=voxel_size, log=False)\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=[10, 4])\n",
    "ax[0].bar(data.bin_centers, data.cdf, data.bin_widths, edgecolor='k');\n",
    "ax[0].set_title(\"PDF scaling included in the result\");\n",
    "data = ps.metrics.pore_size_distribution(im=im, log=False)\n",
    "ax[1].bar(data.bin_centers*voxel_size, data.cdf, data.bin_widths*voxel_size, edgecolor='k');\n",
    "ax[1].set_title(\"PDF scaling after the result\");"
   ]
  }
 ],
